            "prompt": "A git push just completed in the trend-korea project. Save a concise work summary to auto-memory.\n\nSteps:\n1. Run `git log --oneline -5` to see recent commits\n2. Run `git diff HEAD~3..HEAD --stat` for changed files summary\n3. Write a memory file to C:/Users/허우진/.claude/projects/C--dev-trend-korea/memory/ with filename push_YYYY-MM-DD.md (use `date +%Y-%m-%d` for the date). If file exists for today, use push_YYYY-MM-DD_2.md etc.\n4. Use this format:\n   ---\n   name: Push YYYY-MM-DD\n   description: <one-line summary>\n   type: project\n   ---\n   <2-3 bullet points: what changed and why>\n5. Read MEMORY.md from the same directory and add a one-line index entry for the new file.\n\nKeep summary under 80 words. Focus on WHAT and WHY, not HOW.",
